You are implementing `app/api/jobs/[id]/stream/route.ts`, the SSE streaming API route for real-time job progress in a video production pipeline editor.

Requirements
1. `GET /api/jobs/[id]/stream` — opens an SSE `ReadableStream`:
   - Subscribes to job log events by polling the DB every 200ms.
   - Sends new log lines as `data: {"type":"log","message":"..."}\n\n` events.
   - Tracks `lastLineIndex` to only send new lines since last poll.
   - When job reaches `done` status: sends `event: done\ndata: {}\n\n` and closes the stream.
   - When job reaches `error` status: sends `event: error\ndata: {"message":"..."}\n\n` and closes.
2. SSE response headers: `Content-Type: text/event-stream`, `Cache-Control: no-cache`, `Connection: keep-alive`.
3. No authentication required.
4. Export `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`.

